name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

dealinfo: It's a one-night comedy tournament and you and your fellow audience members will determine the fates of the comics at  Comedy Machine Oakland. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: 3KB Sports Bar
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - "TMI Storytelling": True Tales With No Boundaries
dealinfo: Raw stories and real spit rule the mic during  TMI Storytelling , an unpolished monthly show inspired by  The Moth  and  Snap Judgment. Bay Area comedian Gina Gold hosts this comedic series, which covers funny, provocative topics and features a rotating cast of burlesque performers, musicians, circus contortionists and storytellers giving a unadulterated, often hardcore look at life. You'll hear 10-minute tales of heartbreak and woe, peppered with humorous asides and serious commentary highlighting a new theme each month. You might even take home a door prize giveaway at  TMI Storytelling  at 3KB Sports Bar.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: The staff at Bissap Baobab believes dining out should be a full cultural experience. dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealtitle: COMP  for $16.50 - Punch Line Comedy Club Presents Comedy Allstars
dealinfo: Forget the usual dinner-and-a-movie and head out for a night of laughs instead. Punch Line Comedy Club, San Francisco's longest-running stand-up venue, presents Comedy Allstars, featuring a rotating lineup of hilarious stand-up comics from the Bay Area and beyond, including top local headliners to up-and-coming stars and comedians with national TV credits. With stars such as Robin Williams, Ellen Degeneres, Rosie O'Donnell, Drew Carey, Chris Rock and more having cut their comedy teeth at the Punch Line, you never know when you're going to see the next big name in comedy.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

dealinfo: Raw stories and real spit rule the mic during  TMI Storytelling , an unpolished monthly show inspired by  The Moth  and  Snap Judgment. Bay Area comedian Gina Gold hosts this comedic series, which covers funny, provocative topics and features a rotating cast of burlesque performers, musicians, circus contortionists and storytellers giving a unadulterated, often hardcore look at life. You'll hear 10-minute tales of heartbreak and woe, peppered with humorous asides and serious commentary highlighting a new theme each month. You might even take home a door prize giveaway at  TMI Storytelling  at 3KB Sports Bar.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

The comedy rumble will be hosted by comics Ira Summer and Samson "Mahatma Moses" Koletar, who's known as "the world's only Indian Jewish stand-up comedian. " The lineup of contenders will change each night, so this is one you'll want to come to again and again.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

name: 3KB Sports Bar
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - "TMI Storytelling": True Tales With No Boundaries
dealinfo: Raw stories and real spit rule the mic during  TMI Storytelling , an unpolished monthly show inspired by  The Moth  and  Snap Judgment. Bay Area comedian Gina Gold hosts this comedic series, which covers funny, provocative topics and features a rotating cast of burlesque performers, musicians, circus contortionists and storytellers giving a unadulterated, often hardcore look at life. You'll hear 10-minute tales of heartbreak and woe, peppered with humorous asides and serious commentary highlighting a new theme each month. You might even take home a door prize giveaway at  TMI Storytelling  at 3KB Sports Bar.

name: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater
dealtitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Percussive Clown Unique Derique's "Fool La La": Outrageous Show From One Cool Entertainer
dealinfo: Best known for his hilariously inventive "hamboning" technique -- turning his entire body into a percussive instrument -- beloved Bay Area fool Unique Derique brings his fun holiday extravaganza,  Fool La La , to The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater in San Francisco. Whether he's riding a unicycle, juggling or creating infectious rhythms with his body, Unique Derique is one cool clown. Combining outrageous skits with his unique brand of physical comedy, Derique "leaves them laughing coast to coast" ( The San Francisco Examiner ). With TV appearances ranging from the Disney Channel to  Showtime at the Apollo , Derique has entertained audiences of all ages. He's even shared the stage with such entertainers as The Temptations and Sammy Davis Jr.

name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealtitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Inappropriate in All the Right Ways": Solo Show & Workshop With Ann Randolph
dealinfo: From spending time in a mental institution in Appalachia to creating and starring in an off-Broadway solo show produced by Mel Brooks and the late Anne Bancroft, playwright and performer Ann Randolph has lived a life worth telling about. Her latest one-person, multi-character comedy show,  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways , chronicles her journey from her hometown of Loveland, Ohio to the present day, during which she pretended to clean up the Exxon oil spill in Alaska with a bunch of good old boys from Louisiana, experienced a homeless shelter in Santa Monica, and embarked on other adventures as she found her way in the world. Admission to  Inappropriate in All the Right Ways  includes a post-performance workshop with Randolph on following your own passion.

name: Yoshi's Oakland
dealtitle: $89.00 for $89.00 - The Ann Wilson Thing: Heart Singer in Solo Blues Show
dealinfo: Here's the thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- it's a rare chance to see one of the greatest vocalists in rock history singing the low-down dirty blues and more in an intimate setting, and putting her own retro cool spin on favorites by Buffalo Springfield and others. Wilson is, of course, best known as one-half of the legendary sister act Heart, and is responsible for huge hits like "Crazy on You," "Barracuda," "Magic Man," "Dog & Butterfly," "Straight On," "Alone" and more. But at Yoshi's Oakland, she'll be showing off her unmatched vocal power and range on a wide variety of interesting tunes. And here's another thing about The Ann Wilson Thing -- whatever she sings, it's definitely going to be from the heart.

name: The Spinnaker
dealtitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Advanced Degrees Singles Party at The Spinnaker
dealinfo: It's hard for well-educated singles to meet compatible romantic partners -- perhaps because only 7 percent of Americans have an advanced degree. Whether you're continuing your quest to discover your true match or planning to turn over a new leaf by getting yourself out there, you'll meet a bevy of new single friends with doctoral or masters degrees at this sophisticated event. The night kicks off with a fun mixer game, making it easy to meet people, and includes appetizers. The Society of Single Professionals, the largest non-profit singles organization in the world, is sponsoring so there's bound to be a great mix of people at this party at the waterfront Spinnaker restaurant in Sausalito. Make sure you dress to impress.

dealinfo: Raw stories and real spit rule the mic during  TMI Storytelling , an unpolished monthly show inspired by  The Moth  and  Snap Judgment.
